
Jenkins Master Slave configuraiton --
Create VMs 
1. Master-Jenkins-VM , OS Ubuntu (GCP)
2. slave-jekins-VM, OS Ubuntu (GCP)
3. slave-jenkins-vm os windows server on AWS

Install Jenkins and configure on Master-Jenskins-VM

sudo apt update && sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y

sudo wget -O /etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc   https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2026.key
echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc]"   https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee   /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y jenkins
systemctl status jenkins
-- Condifugure Jenkins
 The first Jenkins agent is configured on a Windows Server 2025 VM in AWS, with the workspace located at:
C:\jenkins\developer
Install Java on Windows Server.

2slave-jekins-VM, OS Ubuntu (GCP)
6. The second Jenkins agent is configured on a VM running Ubuntu 24.04 LTS in GCP, with the workspace located at:
/var/jenkins/performance
Install Java on sever
